title: Why I almost get caught and then get put on blast 🤦🏽‍♂️ #skit #shorts #viral #explore #shortvideos
#movie 🔪 Betrayal and Brutality: The Infamous Stabbing Scene from "Chopper"
description:
The ultimate act of betrayal happens when violence comes from the one you trust most. In this scene breakdown, we're diving into one of the most raw and shocking moments from the gritty Australian crime biopic, "Chopper" (2000). This film pulls no punches in its portrayal of notorious criminal Mark "Chopper" Read, but this particular scene delivers a gut-wrenching blow—literally.

The Setup: A Tense Reunion
The scene builds on a classic yet volatile dynamic: the tense reunion between old friends. Mark "Chopper" Read (played with unnerving intensity by Eric Bana), now out of prison, meets up with a former friend and associate. There's history here—shared time behind bars, old scores, and the unspoken rules of the criminal world. The atmosphere is thick with unspoken threats and past grievances. Chopper, ever the provocateur, might be testing boundaries, while his friend simmers with a resentment that's about to boil over.

The Betrayal: When a Friend Becomes the Weapon
What makes the violence so impactful is its origin. This isn't a random act from a stranger; it's a calculated, deeply personal attack from someone who was once considered a "good friend". The argument escalates, and in a flash, the friend produces a knife. The ensuing attack is brutal, frenzied, and visceral. Chopper is stabbed multiple times—a relentless assault that is as much about emotional betrayal as it is physical harm. The cinematography doesn't glorify the violence; it traps you in the chaos, making you feel the shock and the violation of trust.

Why This Scene is Iconic

Eric Bana's Breakout Performance: This scene is a masterclass in Bana's physical commitment. He portrays the shock, the adrenaline-fueled survival instinct, and the profound hurt of betrayal with terrifying authenticity.

The Core of Chopper's Myth: This moment is pivotal to understanding Chopper Read's legend. It's a key incident that fuels his paranoia, his ruthless reputation, and the cycle of violence that defines his life. It shows that in his world, even the closest bonds can be severed with a blade.

More Than Just a Stabbing: The scene transcends a simple act of violence. It's a dark exploration of loyalty, power, and the fragile codes of the underworld. It asks a haunting question: what happens when the rules break down and the person you'd trust with your life is the one trying to end it?

This brutal betrayal is a cornerstone of the film's exploration of crime not as glamour, but as a brutal, isolating, and psychologically damaging way of life.

What do you think is the ultimate betrayal in cinema? Is it worse when it comes from a friend or a loved one? Let us know your thoughts in the comments below.

If you're fascinated by the gritty, true-crime stories that Hollywood rarely tells, be sure to LIKE, SUBSCRIBE, and hit the bell for more deep dives into the most hard-hitting scenes from cult classics and biopics.

title: POV: Choosing Between Jupiter and Mars PT2 😳🔥 #pov #comedy #shorts #animation #humor
description: you’ve made it to Part 2, and the decision is still not easy. Jupiter is huge, a gas giant, perfect for big parties and exploring its stormy atmosphere, but Mars has the allure of being the closest and full of mystery. You weigh the pros and cons, and suddenly realize you have no idea what you’d actually do on either planet. Jupiter might crush you with its pressure, and Mars might freeze you to death, but hey, they look cool in the animation. You ask your friend for advice, and they suggest you choose Earth instead, but then you remember you have no idea what that place is like either. You finally make a decision, but it’s more about avoiding the pressure than any real love for the planets.

title: Comment la prise d’otages du plus gros studio de youtubeurs a dégénéré ? - Épisode 2
description:
Profitez de 20 euros offerts en ETF avec Trade Republic sur ce lien ► https://trade.re/ludoc20
Conditions: créditez 100€ et faire 3 investissements sous 21 jours  
Investir comporte des risques, notamment le risque de perte de capital. Les performances passées ne préjugent pas les performances futures. Collaboration commerciale avec Trade Republic. Conditions et informations disponibles sur l'application Trade Republic

Episode 1 : https://youtu.be/XexpNOZHh7g

Synopsis :

La prise d’otages dans le plus grand studio de youtubeurs dégénère, le forcené devient de plus en plus fou et agressif. Plusieurs médias dévoilent l’existence d’une deuxième otage cachée. La BRI et les sapeurs pompiers n’ont plus le choix et doivent lancer un assaut d’urgence. 

Le 12 juin 2018, au cœur de Paris, une prise d’otages éclate dans les bureaux de Mixicom, l’agence de Cyprien, Squeezie et de plusieurs des plus grands youtubeurs français. Ce qui ressemble d’abord à un acte de folie isolé révèle rapidement un tout autre scénario : le forcené n’est pas là par hasard, il vise les créateurs de l’agence.

À travers les témoignages exclusifs des survivants, des négociateurs de la BRI, des enregistrements audios et des archives inédites, cette série documentaire reconstitue minute par minute le déroulement de ces quatre heures de siège. Un récit sous haute tension qui explore les mécanismes de la violence, la fascination pour la notoriété et les limites de la justice face à la maladie mentale.

Avec les interventions de Adrien Gabeaud, Christophe Molmy, Nicolas de la BRI, Georges Salinas, Sandrine Larremendy, Franck Bonnier, David-Olivier Reverdy, Johanna Rozenblum, Karine Jean, Christian Sainte, Michel Delpuech, Rudy Reichstadt, Dr Bilal Bendid, Dr Vincent Mahé et Christophe de la Police Judiciaire.

Les enregistrements audio, les images de l'intervention, les vidéos des riverains et les extraits télévisés présentés dans ce documentaire sont authentiques. Certaines images de vidéosurveillance et vues aériennes sont des reconstitutions basées sur des recherches et des témoignages directs. Les noms de certains intervenants ont été volontairement masqués afin de préserver leur anonymat, conformément à leur souhait.

Joyeux Noël est un film français de 2005 sur l'histoire de la trêve de noël 1914 entre l'Armée Française et les soldats Allemands. Dans cette scène culte et virale du film, un officier Allemand invite les soldats français à venir se cacher dans la tranchée de l'Empire Allemand afin d'éviter de perdre des hommes à cause de l'artillerie. description:
Anime : The Strongest Sage with the Weakest Crest

Dans un monde où la puissance magique est déterminée par des emblèmes de naissance, le sage Gaius est le plus puissant du monde. Cependant, il estime que son emblème n'est pas adapté au combat pur. Pour devenir encore plus fort, il décide de se réincarner des milliers d'années dans le futur.

Il renaît sous le nom de Mathias avec l'emblème qu'il désirait tant. Mais il découvre avec stupeur que dans ce futur, la connaissance de la magie a régressé et que son emblème est désormais considéré comme le "plus faible". En utilisant ses connaissances de sa vie antérieure, Mathias va rapidement prouver que le monde se trompe lourdement.

The UNLIKELIEST Superhero Tryouts | Zoom's Academy Scene
description:
Video Description:

Forget the Justice League. This superhero team is recruited from detention! In the 2006 comedy Zoom, a secret government program needs to train a new generation of heroes. Their leader, former hero Captain Zoom, is tasked with finding candidates with a specific genetic marker.

He finds them in the most unexpected place: a group of misfit teenagers. One by one, they are brought to the underground academy. Watch the hilarious and surprising moment each kid reveals their unique, often clumsy power: one can run at supersonic speed but can't stop, another has super-strength tied to his emotions, a girl can turn invisible when she's embarrassed, and another can manipulate objects with her mind.

Their "tryout" is pure chaos—a perfect mix of slapstick and super-powered potential. Against all odds, this ragtag group of outcasts is officially enrolled as Earth's new last line of defense. It’s a funny, feel-good clip about finding power where you least expect it.

Why Watch?

· Fun Superhero Twist: A lighthearted, comedic take on the classic "hero origin" story.
· Underrated Cast: Features a young cast including Kate Mara and a fun performance from Tim Allen.
· Pure 2000s Fun: A nostalgic dose of family-friendly action-comedy.

title: 😱 "The Last Frontier" | The Tank Assault That BROKE the Last Cadets! 🐅💥
description:
😱 "The Last Frontier" | The Tank Assault That BROKE the Last Cadets! 🐅💥

The German war machine unleashes hell. Stuka dive-bombers shatter the earth, artillery turns trenches into graves, and then the true horror arrives: a rolling wave of Panzer tanks in a deadly wedge formation. They crash through barbed wire, crush bunkers, and their machine guns mow down young cadets like wheat. 😨🔥

What follows is a slaughter of heartbreaking, futile heroism. 🫡

Anti-tank gunners are obliterated the moment they fire.

Cadets with bundles of grenades charge forward, only to be cut down by machine-gun fire before they can reach their target.

Officers scream orders to blow the bridges, sending sappers on suicide missions through a storm of steel.

This scene is a visceral, brutal, and tragic depiction of mechanized warfare — where youth and courage are ground to dust under tank treads. 🎬⚙️💔

#movie Hubert Fiorentini vs. Three Goons | Wasabi (2001) Fight Scene Breakdown
description:
Hey everyone, and welcome back to the channel! In today's scene breakdown, we're diving into a classic action-comedy from the early 2000s that blends French bravado with Japanese chaos. We're looking at "Wasabi" (also known as The Avenging Fist or Green Mustard), starring the legendary Jean Reno.

This 2001 film, written by the master of Euro-action Luc Besson, follows Hubert Fiorentini (Jean Reno), a tough, no-nonsense Parisian cop with a notoriously short fuse and a heavy heart over a lost love. When he travels to Tokyo to settle the affairs of his late ex-girlfriend, he gets the shock of his life: he has a 19-year-old daughter, Yumi (played by Ryoko Hirosue). His mission to reconnect with her is immediately hijacked when they discover Yumi is the target of violent Japanese yakuza, who are after a massive fortune left in her name.

The Scene: A Father's Instincts Kick In
The clip we're breaking down today is a perfect example of Hubert's character. He's trying to have a normal day with his newly discovered, shopping-obsessed daughter in the bustling streets of Tokyo. However, his sharp cop instincts immediately sense they are being followed by hostile figures.

What unfolds is a masterclass in efficient, brutal action. Three yakuza enforcers, thinking they have the upper hand, move in to confront or kidnap Yumi. They severely underestimate the man beside her. In a flash, the shopping bags are dropped. The gentle, awkward father persona vanishes, and the hardened police detective takes over.

Why This Fight is Iconic

Character in Action: This isn't just a random fight. It visually communicates Hubert's core trait: he protects what's his with overwhelming force. It's his violent, love language.

Comedic Contrast: The scene thrives on the stark contrast. One moment it's a quirky father-daughter outing, the next it's a whirlwind of precise, painful-looking takedowns. The comedy comes from the sheer nonchalance with which Hubert dispatches the threat before returning to "dad mode".

Jean Reno's Presence: No one does "gruff exterior with a secret soft spot" quite like Jean Reno. He brings a physical credibility and a weary, "I don't have time for this" attitude that makes the action both cool and funny.

A Nod to Léon: For fans of Reno's iconic role in Léon: The Professional, this film and this scene feel like a fun, alternate-universe sequel where the protector finally gets a happy, action-packed family life.

This scene sets the tone for the entire film: a chaotic, funny, and heartfelt journey where a French bruiser uses his very particular set of skills to clean up the Tokyo underworld for the sake of family.

What's your favorite Jean Reno action role? Is it Hubert from Wasabi, the iconic Léon, or someone else? Let's chat in the comments below!

Don't forget to LIKE this video if you enjoyed the breakdown, and SUBSCRIBE for more deep dives into classic action movie moments every week!

title: #movie Ready for an action scene where a single man takes down an entire security team in close
description:
Ready for an action scene where a single man takes down an entire security team in close quarters? 🎬

In this intense sequence from "3 Days to Kill," legendary CIA operative Ethan Renner (Kevin Costner) infiltrates an apartment to extract a key target. What he finds is a room full of heavily armed bodyguards, ready for a fight.

Watch as the seasoned but ailing agent uses his environment, quick thinking, and sheer force of will to turn the tables in a brutal and confined firefight. It's a masterclass in close-quarters combat from a man who has nothing left to lose but everything to gain.

What is "3 Days to Kill" about?
Ethan Renner is a veteran international spy diagnosed with a terminal illness. Ready to retire and reconnect with his estranged family, he is pulled back in for one last mission by a mysterious handler, Vivi (Amber Heard). She offers him an experimental drug that could save his life in exchange for taking down "The Wolf," one of the world's most dangerous terrorists. Now, Ethan must balance this deadly assignment with the even harder job of being a father to his teenage daughter for the first time in years.

description:
When the Prince of Darkness needs to secure a London property deal, he doesn't send a bat… he sends a lawyer. 💼In this brilliantly bizarre scene from Francis Ford Coppola's Bram Stoker's Dracula (1992), Count Dracula (Gary Oldman) proves his cunning extends beyond supernatural powers. Having arrived in London, he employs a unique agent—a sinister, pale "lawyer"—to finalize the purchase of Carfax Abbey with the unsuspecting Jonathan Harker.The Perfect Disguise: The "lawyer" is widely understood to be one of Dracula's vampire brides in disguise, showcasing his ability to manipulate human society from within.Gothic Atmosphere: The scene drips with eerie tension, blending Victorian formalities with an underlying sense of dread and otherworldly menace.

Totally Spies 😂
#movie A King's Man's Daring Escape | "The Goat Pull" Scene Breakdown
description:
Forget high-tech gadgets—this might just be the most unconventional, utterly ridiculous, and weirdly brilliant escape plan in Kingsman history!

In this wild scene from The King's Man, the film that explores the origins of the iconic Kingsman spy organization during World War I, the hero finds himself in a desperate situation . It perfectly captures the series' signature blend of high-stakes action and dark comedy.

Here, Orlando, the Duke of Oxford (played by Ralph Fiennes), is trapped on the side of a sheer cliff after a brutal fight with the film's villain . With options running out, survival comes down to sheer wit... and the help of an unlikely ally. In a moment of pure, inspired desperation, he uses a mountain goat as his unlikely ladder, stepping on its back and pulling on its horns to hoist himself to the top of the cliff .

This scene is a prime example of how this prequel film differentiates itself. While forgoing the futuristic weapons of the later films, it delivers jaw-dropping action through wildly creative and sometimes illogical physical feats set against the backdrop of the Great War . It's a tense, funny, and completely unexpected moment that reminds us why we love this franchise.

What to Watch For:

The Setup: The brutal fight on the clifftop that leaves the hero dangling for his life.

The "Solution": The calm yet absurd moment of realization as Orlando spots the goat and formulates his plan.

The Execution: The sheer physicality and suspense of the climb.

The Aftermath: The now-iconic moment where, having reached safety, he shares a long, bewildered stare with the goat that just saved him .

Don't forget to LIKE, SUBSCRIBE, and hit the BELL for more breakdowns of the most inventive, funny, and badass scenes from your favorite action movies!

What did you think of this scene? Was it genius or just plain silly? Let us know in the comments below!

title: Pourquoi avoir créer un gant de droitier... Contrairement au gant de l'infini ?
description:
Pourquoi avoir créer un gant de droitier... Contrairement au gant de l'infini ?

Nous analysons comment les Russo Brothers et leur scénariste Steve McFeely ont méticuleusement construit l'arc narratif de Tony Stark à travers le MCU. Nous explorons comment les blessures répétées au bras gauche de Tony, depuis Iron Man jusqu'à Endgame, ont été des indices subtils menant à sa décision cruciale de créer un gant de l'infini pour droitier plutôt que pour gaucher. Nous montrons comment chaque détail, des tremblements de sa main à la bandoulière qu'il porte, s'interconnecte pour justifier son choix final et son sacrifice ultime.

description:
In Superman IV: The Quest for Peace (1987), Clark Kent endures mockery at the gym as an instructor tries to humiliate him in front of Lacy, poking fun at his “lack” of fitness.

Staying in character, Clark plays the awkward, harmless reporter — until Lacy looks away.

In one perfectly timed “accident,” Clark casually tosses a massive barbell at the mouthy instructor, sending him crashing to the floor.

With classic deadpan delivery, Clark caps it off with one of the film’s funniest lines:

“No pain, no gain.”

A reminder that even as Clark Kent, Superman never forgets how to make a point.

C'est la dernière soirée où j't'emmène

J'en ai rien à faire de te perdre

F-150 Raptor vs. Ranger Raptor: Not Just a Size Difference!

The Ford F-150 Raptor was designed around American demands. Full-size proportions, massive bed space, integrated tailgate steps, and hardware meant for towing, hauling, and wide-open terrain.

The Ford Ranger Raptor, built for Europe, prioritizes maneuverability and efficiency. It’s smaller, lighter, and engineered for tighter roads, stricter regulations, and different use cases altogether

Think all Raptors are created equal? Think again

title: Fabriquer une Lamborghini chez soi 🔥
description:
Il a fabriqué une Lamborghini avec une imprimante 3D, mais au lieu de porter plainte, Lamborghini a fait quelque chose d’incroyable.

Il a commencé le projet il y a 5 ans avec son fils.
Ils ont fabriqué eux-mêmes la structure de la voiture et ont produit les panneaux de carrosserie avec une imprimante 3D.
Quand est venu le moment du volant, comme celui de Lamborghini était cher, ils ont utilisé un volant Audi.

Pendant ce temps, Lamborghini a remarqué la voiture et, au lieu de porter plainte, a fait exactement le contraire.
Ils leur ont offert le volant, les phares et les feux arrière.

title: 🔥 Ferrari réinvente l’avenir du transport avec son camion futuriste
description: 🔥 Ferrari réinvente l’avenir du transport avec son camion futuriste. Ce camion Ferrari incarne une nouvelle vision de la puissance et du luxe, mêlant design audacieux, technologie avancée et performance iconique. Fidèle à l’ADN Ferrari, chaque ligne est sculptée pour l’aérodynamisme, chaque détail respire la vitesse et l’excellence italienne. À l’intérieur, un cockpit ultra-moderne dominé par un pare-brise panoramique immense offre une immersion totale sur la route. Écrans numériques, commandes tactiles, éclairage LED subtil et matériaux premium comme le carbone et le cuir créent une atmosphère futuriste et cinématographique. Sur la route, le camion Ferrari se déplace avec une fluidité hypnotique, transformant chaque instant en une expérience visuelle satisfaisante. Ce n’est pas juste un camion… c’est une vision du futur signée Ferrari. #Ferrari#ConceptCar #LuxuryVehicle #Cinematic #POV #FutureTransport #CarLovers #SuperTruck #HighTech #DreamVehicle #ViralCars #TikTokCars #YouTubeShorts #AutoConcept #CarAesthetic

136 MPH with Just 100 HP? The Aerodynamic Cheat Code! 🤯
description:
136 MPH with just 1.0 litre? Meet the Abarth “Principessa” – the aerodynamic masterpiece that shattered 9 world records in 1960! 🤯 This is the 1960 Fiat-Abarth 1000 Monoposto da Record, affectionately known as “La Principessa” (The Princess). Designed by Pininfarina and developed in the Turin Polytechnic wind tunnels, this silver needle was a hand-sculpted technical marvel.

At just 1.2 meters tall and over 4.5 meters long, every curve was engineered to slice through the air on the Monza Autodrome’s high-speed oval. Its tiny 1.0-litre twin-cam engine produced around 108 HP, pushing the car to a top speed of 136 mph (220 km/h) and breaking nine international world records, including a 72-hour endurance run averaging 187 km/h.

Legendary driver Umberto Maglioli even pushed the car across the finish line by hand in heavy rain during the record attempt—securing Abarth’s place in automotive history. Today, “La Principessa” is an unrestored time capsule and one of the most valuable classics in existence, valued at $1–1.5 million.

Watch, listen, and marvel at the aerodynamic cheat code of a bygone era.

#abarth #pininfarina #vintagecars #automotivehistory #worldrecords #carenthusiast #topspeed #carshorts #engineeringmarvel #carhistory

title: Fastest Traffic Stop?
description:
The Fastest Traffic Stop in Europe?

​The Netherlands is officially leveling up its highway patrol.
To keep up with high-speed chases and complex traffic enforcement, the Dutch police are now testing the ultimate interceptor: the BMW K1600GT-P.
​
Why this bike is a game-changer:
​
The Heart of a Beast: It’s powered by a massive 1,649cc inline-six engine that delivers a smooth yet terrifying 160 horsepower.  
​
Precision Handling: Despite its size, the low center of gravity makes it one of the most agile touring bikes on the planet—perfect for weaving through Dutch traffic.  
​
Tactical Tech: This isn't your standard tourer.
The "P" (Police) variant is outfitted with integrated emergency lighting, sirens, and advanced communication systems to facilitate rapid traffic stops.
​
Speed & Stability: With a top speed of over 200 km/h, there aren't many vehicles on the A10 that can outrun this six-cylinder powerhouse.
​
Would you pull over immediately if you saw this six-cylinder monster in your rearview mirror, or do you think a smaller, lighter bike is better for police work?

title: Mercedes Final Boss 600 Build: From Rusty Relic to 1,000HP Beast in Under 5 Months
description:
Witness the engineering triumph of the Final Boss 600: a restomod integrating a 1971 Mercedes-Benz 600 Grosser body with a 2024 Mercedes-AMG S 63 E Performance chassis, yielding over 1,000 hp and 1,000 lb-ft via a 4.0L twin-turbo V8 plug-in hybrid. Executed by S-Klub LA under 5 months total for SEMA 2025, this build fuses classic design with contemporary dynamics. Here’s the technical breakdown, step by step.

Step 1: Donor Procurement – Acquired a new S 63 E Performance (802 hp stock, 1,050 lb-ft, 4MATIC+ AWD, Executive Rear Package). Matched with a short-wheelbase 1971 600 shell from Texas, leveraging near-identical 126-inch wheelbase for seamless integration.

Step 2: Disassembly and Structural Prep – Sandblasted the 1971 body to expose and repair corrosion; substituted hydraulic systems with electric window mechanisms for mass reduction. Deconstructed the S 63 to isolate chassis, powertrain (including AMG Ride Control+ suspension and rear-axle steering), and interior components.

Step 3: Platform Fusion and Modifications – Affixed the 1971 shell to the S 63 chassis, extending rear glazing by 2 inches for suspension compatibility. Engineered widened fenders for widebody architecture; integrated carbon fiber roof, mirrors, and spoiler. Developed 3D-scanned, AI-optimized LED headlights with S 63 modules in bespoke printed housings—spanning 3 months, executed in parallel with grill assembly incorporating LiDAR and emblem integration. Added rear wing, hood vents, mirrors, and HRE wheels. Body engineering phase: two months.

Step 4: Surface and Systems Refinement – Primed and applied metallic green coating. Merged S 63 taillights with McLaren 675LT LED arrays; enhanced audio via Voch 2 amplifiers; fitted Anti-Gravity lithium battery. Preserved AMG interior: Nappa leather seating.

Step 5: Integration and Validation – Finalized wiring and assembly in a 6-day intensive; performed initial shakedown drive pre-SEMA. Delivered to Toyo Tires Tread Pass for unveiling and SEMA Cruise.

title: These Engines Only Last 4 Seconds
description:
Nitro Funny Car racing isn’t just one 4-second pass—it’s a full-scale rebuild in between every round. 💨

After a run, the car comes straight back to the pits and gets torn down. Engine out, clutch out, heads off, valves checked, rods inspected, bearings swapped, clutch pack rebuilt, fuel system serviced—everything is inspected and refreshed because 12,000+ horsepower on 90% nitromethane doesn’t forgive mistakes.

Teams have roughly 60–90 minutes to completely rebuild the car, warm it up, and get it back to the staging lanes for the next round. That warm-up isn’t for show—it’s a controlled explosion to check timing, fuel flow, clutch setup, and data before strapping the driver back in.

Then it’s back to the line, strap in, stage, and send it—330+ mph in under four seconds, riding the edge of traction, engine life, and physics itself.

This is NHRA Funny Car racing: controlled chaos, relentless precision, and a crew working at full throttle between rounds.

For full engine rebuilds, pit footage, and raw behind-the-scenes content, check out our channel @chadgreenmotorsports 
#nhra #chadgreen #chadgreenmotorsports

title: Is This the World's First Safety Car?
description:
Step back in time to 1926 to witness one of the most unusual automotive experiments in history! This rare archive footage shows the inventor André Mercier and his "Acrobatic Auto" during a series of controlled tests in France.

Designed with a unique circular chassis, the Mercier car was engineered to be "uncrashable." The goal was to create a vehicle that could roll over and return to its wheels without injuring the driver or destroying the engine—a visionary precursor to the modern roll cage.

This video is shared for historical and educational purposes only. The stunts shown were performed by a professional inventor in a controlled setting for engineering demonstrations nearly 100 years ago. Do not attempt to replicate these maneuvers with modern vehicles.

#VintageCars #EngineeringHistory #1920s #AutomotiveInnovation #colorised

description:
This exhaust manifold stud is rusted and seized. To remove it, we’re using our GripEdge G-FORS Socket Extractor.

Its straight-cut, non-tapered design provides bi-directional control, allowing you to both tighten and loosen the fastener or stud to help break it free. That added control is key when dealing with stubborn, corroded, or seized hardware to prevent it from snapping off.

title: The Last Goblina
description:
When hearts break, heroes rise. From lost love to forged power, this is the legend of the last Goblina, and the tragedy that changed Mega Minion and Goblin forever.

X ► https://twitter.com/ClashRoyale/
Instagram ► https://www.instagram.com/clashroyale
TikTok ► https://www.tiktok.com/@clashroyale
Facebook ► https://www.facebook.com/ClashRoyale/

ENTER THE ARENA
Build your Battle Deck and outsmart the enemy in fast real-time battles. From the creators of CLASH OF CLANS comes a real-time multiplayer battle game starring your favourite Clash characters and more. Start battling against players from around the world!

BECOME A MASTER OF STRATEGY AND DECK BUILDING
Choose unique Cards to your Battle Deck and head to the Arena for Battle!
Place your Cards right and knock down the enemy King and Tower Troops from their Towers in a strategic and fast-paced match.

COLLECT AND UPGRADE 100+ CARDS
Hog Rider! Collect and upgrade 100+ Cards featuring the Clash of Clans troops, spells and defences you know and love and many others. Win battles and progress to new Arenas to unlock powerful new Cards to your collection!

BATTLE YOUR WAY TO THE TOP
Battle your way to the League and Global Tournaments to match against the best players in the world.
Compete for glory and rewards!

SEASONAL EVENTS
Unlock new Seasonal items like Tower Skins, Emotes and powerful Magic Items with the Season Pass and participate in fun Challenges that put your skills to the test!

JOIN A CLAN AND GO TO WAR
Join or form a Clan with other players to share Cards and battle in Clan Wars for BIG rewards!

See you in the Arena!
#ClashRoyale

title: KARMA : le jeu qui brise ton cœur et ton cerveau.
description:
KARMA : le jeu que a réussie à me briser. 

ATTENTION TRIGGER WARNING : Si vous êtes sensibles à certains sujets tel que de la violence de tout type, impliquant des personnes majeures ou mineurs, ou que vous vous sentez mal à l'aise en regardant cette vidéo, merci d'interrompre le visionnage de cette dernière, votre santé est plus important que tout prenez soin de vous ❤️🫶

Nom du jeu : Karma The Dark World

Contactes : 
https://x.com/ManjiroSayNo
https://discord.gg/mnCPQ2ncqg

Musique de fin : wifiskeleton - my twenty first reason ˂/3

L'illustration de la miniature a été faite par l'incroyable Kimi !!! Voici son X : https://x.com/kimipatisserie


NOTE A MOI:
Je suis vraiment désolé pour l'attente, j'ai eu pas mal de soucis au niveau personnel et mental durant l'hivers (décembre) et je me sentais vraiment pas bien pour écrire/rec ma voix ou même monter donc j'ai préférer faire tout ça quand j'allais bien. Maintenant que c'est passé je suis chaud pour continuer mon aventure dans la création de contenu !! Concernant cette vidéo franchement je l'aime bien, c'était assez long et fastidieux comme travail mais le rendu est vraiment cool, je pense pas que la vidéo vas rencontrer un énorme succès car c'est surement pas ce qu'une majorité de personnes aiment mais je trouve que tout de même c'est une très bonne vidéo, mon seul point de réticence c'est l'utilisation de cinématique, j'ai peur que ça fasse "trop" mais en même temps elles sont si belles que j'étais obligé de les mettre, et ça fais plus un format "film" du coup, c'est surement pas au gout de tout le monde mais c'est la meilleur option pour "adapter" un jeu aussi cinématique.

Brawl Stars est un jeu mobile multijoueur développé par Supercell. Il propose des affrontements rapides et dynamiques en 3 contre 3 ou en solo, avec des parties courtes et intenses.
Le joueur incarne des Brawlers, chacun possédant des capacités, attaques et super-pouvoirs uniques. Le jeu offre de nombreux modes de jeu (Razzia de gemmes, Brawl Ball, Survivant, Zone réservée, etc.), renouvelés régulièrement.
Au-delà de l’aspect compétitif, Brawl Stars se distingue par son univers riche et mystérieux, son lore caché, et une forte scène esport internationale. Accessible mais stratégique, le jeu récompense aussi bien la maîtrise individuelle que le travail d’équipe.

title: FALLEN KINGDOMS MODDÉ - SAISON 1 #04 : L'ÉPÉE LA PLUS PUISSANTE EN NEPTUNIUM !
description:
Fallen Kingdoms est de retour dans une nouvelle version moddée promettant encore plus de stratégies et de combats !

Equipe Bleue :    @Bichard   https://www.twitch.tv/rises
Equipe Jaune :   @myrolame   @Flanny  
Equipe Rouge :   @TheGuill84  @Siphano13  

Développeur : https://x.com/Neutron_Stars_
Voix off : https://www.instagram.com/yoannsover
Miniature : https://x.com/Reiko193_
Map : https://discord.gg/mb53cyJmHc

Règles :
 
- Si une équipe perd, elle est dispatchée dans les 2 équipes restantes
- L'ensemble de l'équipe doit trouver la salle des coffres adverse pour gagner
- Un assaut ne peux se faire que si les 2 objectifs sont construits : une salle des coffres et une muraille de 4 de haut
- La salle des coffres a le droit de se situer jusqu'à 20 blocs en dessous de la base. La salle des coffres en hauteur est interdite.
- Il est interdit d'attaquer avec des enderpearls, par des arbres ou des collines autour d'une base. Mais s'échapper d'une base avec est autorisé
- Lors d'un assaut, la muraille et les lits doivent obligatoirement être détruits par des TNT, des creepers ou un wither.
- Une équipe a la possibilité de créer une alliance avec une autre équipe, en s'organisant via un panneau
 
- Le PVP est activé au Jour 2, le Nether est activé au Jour 4 et les Assauts sont autorisés au Jour 7.
- Liste des blocs posables hors de la base : TNT, Torche, Panneaux, Seau d'Eau, Bateaux (sauf dans les bases adverses pour les Seaux)

Les épisodes sont tous tournés avant la diffusion pour éviter le spoil.

description:

title: Starting My 2026 Tactical Shooter Journey With Ghost Recon 2
description:
Tom Clancy’s Ghost Recon 2 is a third-person tactical shooter released for the PlayStation 2 in 2004. The game focuses on squad-based combat, realistic military engagements, and careful planning rather than fast-paced arcade shooting. Players command elite special forces units through hostile environments where positioning, cover, and coordination determine success or failure.

Today we’re kicking off a brand-new nostalgic tactical military journey by revisiting Tom Clancy’s Ghost Recon 2 on the PlayStation 2.

This isn’t just a one-off throwback — this is the start of a full special forces evolution series.

We’re going all the way back to the roots of tactical shooters, where positioning mattered, teamwork mattered, and one bad decision could end a mission instantly. From here, we’ll slowly work our way forward through the history of military shooters  watching how special forces units, technology, tactics, and gameplay design evolve over time.

 The Long-Term Goal
This series will follow a clear progression:
    •    Classic tactical realism
    •    Limited HUD and information
    •    Squad-based decision making
    •    Gradual evolution into modern and futuristic military tech

We’ll be revisiting games like:
    •    SOCOM U.S. Navy SEALs
    •    Early Ghost Recon titles
    •    And eventually progressing into the more modern Ghost Recon entries

Each game represents a snapshot in time — not just for gaming, but for how military operations were imagined, simulated, and presented to players.

 What Makes Ghost Recon 2 Special

Released during the golden era of PlayStation 2 tactical shooters, Ghost Recon 2 emphasizes:
    •    Methodical movement over run-and-gun gameplay
    •    Squad positioning and situational awareness
    •    Realistic engagements where mistakes are punished
    •    Minimal hand-holding compared to modern shooters

This is the era where tactical thinking mattered more than reflexes.

 What to Expect in This Playthrough
    •    First-time revisit with a modern perspective
    •    Tactical decision-making, not speedrunning
    •    Honest reactions to difficulty, pacing, and realism
    •    Comparisons to modern military shooters
    •    A slow, intentional progression through the series

If you love:
    •    Old-school military shooters
    •    Tactical gameplay
    •    Nostalgia with purpose
    •    Seeing how games evolved over time

You’re in the right place.

title: The Sims 4 Royalty & Legacy | Official Dynasty Gameplay Trailer
description:
Build your legacy in The Sims™ 4 Royalty & Legacy Expansion Pack*, available Feb 12 at 10 am PT. Pre-order for the Royal Treasures Digital Content**; the Enemies to Lovers Practice Dummy, A Crown of Leaves and Sparkles, and the Under the Stars Lantern. These items are available through Mar 15.

Pre-order today: https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/buy/addon/the-sims-4-royalty-and-legacy-grand-bundle 

Learn more: https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/news/royalty-and-legacy-expansion-pack

Do it all for the plot. Build a powerful Dynasty, take advantage of Perks, and be the powerhouse family everyone wants to keep up with. Any Sim (Young Adult or over) can start their own Dynasty, complete with a custom name and crest. 

A Dynasty dominates through devotion to shared Values, which are set when the Dynasty Head chooses up to 3 skills and 3 Ideals. When members show that they align with these values – like by joining relevant careers, working on the right skills, or performing related interactions – the Dynasty's Prestige goes up. The higher the Prestige level, the more the Dynasty can take advantage of Perks, like private tutors or Nepotism. When a Sim in a Dynasty does things that conflict with the Dynasty Values, Prestige can go down. 

Prestige can also take a hit when a member is at the center of a Scandal, such as their steamy tryst with a member of a rival Dynasty being exposed or having a secret child. 

Besides the Values, the Head can choose their Heir and declare Outcasts. An Outcast might seek redemption, or they might rebel. An Heir might be overwhelmed by pressure, or they might rise to the occasion. Relationships can get complicated, and how it all plays out is up to you. Maintain Unity to increase the number of positive events the Dynasty sees, or see what drama unfolds when it gets low.

Available February 12 at 10AM PT on EA App PC/Mac, Steam, Xbox One, Xbox Series X|S, PlayStation®4, and PlayStation®5. Pre-order now: https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/buy/addon/the-sims-4-royalty-and-legacy-grand-bundle

*Requires The Sims 4 & all game updates. For PC, see minimum system requirements for the pack.

**CONDITIONS AND RESTRICTIONS APPLY. See https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/buy/addon/the-sims-4-royalty-and-legacy-expansion-pack for details.

Une méthode unique pour laver les moutons ? 🐑 #animaux #shorts
description:
Pourquoi jettent-ils les moutons à la mer ? Ces éleveurs utilisent une méthode de lavage des moutons pour le moins originale.

C'est le moins qu'on puisse dire ! Mais savez-vous ce qui est encore plus efficace ? Les jeter directement dans la mer. Le sel aide les moutons à se débarrasser des parasites et bactéries présents sur leur corps. Bien que les moutons n'apprécient guère la nage, ils s'en sortent plutôt bien.

Grâce à la surveillance des éleveurs, les risques de noyade sont quasi nuls. Des bains réguliers comme celui-ci sont importants pour garantir la qualité de leur laine. Mais que faire s'il n'y a pas de point d'eau à proximité ? Les éleveurs aménagent des bassins artificiels comme celui-ci.

Il s'agit d'un bain pour moutons. C'est une solution aqueuse spéciale contenant un insecticide et un fongicide. Les éleveurs et les bergers utilisent ce bain pour protéger leur troupeau des infestations de parasites externes tels que les acariens, les tiques et les poux.

title: Veronika, une vache d'exception
description: Veronika est une vache exceptionnelle. Elle est capable d’utiliser un outil pour se gratter : un bâton, un balai ou un râteau. À tel point que des scientifiques l’ont étudiée et en ont tiré des conclusions incroyables. Elle est la première bovine à manier consciemment un outil, et à l'adapter à ses besoins. Elle va notamment choisir quelle partie du balai utiliser selon la partie de son corps qui la démange. Les scientifiques notent tout de même qu’elle n’est pas nécessairement plus intelligente qu’une autre et que ses conditions de vie y sont peut-être pour quelque chose.  Veronika a 13 ans et n’est pas destinée à l’élevage, elle vit au cœur des Alpes autrichiennes. La découverte permettra peut-être de bousculer les préjugés sur ces animaux, souvent jugés peu intelligents.

title: Quand il veut fouiller mon téléphone 😱🤣
Ce chien teste l'électricité statique avant de descendre du trampoline ! 🐶⚡️
description:
Lorsque les chiens sautent sur un trampoline, de l'électricité statique peut s'accumuler à cause de la friction. Lorsque le tapis du trampoline s'étire et frotte contre la fourrure du chien, les électrons se transfèrent entre les surfaces, créant de l'énergie statique.

L'air sec rend cela encore plus fort, car l'humidité aide normalement l'électricité à se dissiper. C'est pourquoi les poils peuvent se hérisser ou de petites étincelles peuvent parfois être ressenties après avoir sauté.

C'est la même raison pour laquelle vous pourriez recevoir un choc après avoir sauté sur un trampoline ou touché un objet métallique. Juste de la science, plus un très bon chien.

title: The zoo went bankrupt so employees pretended to be animals 😆
description:
Secret Zoo (2020) became a surprise hit not only for its heartwarming story but also for the unusual amount of physical comedy training the actors had to go through. Since many of the main characters spend large portions of the film inside full body animal suits, the cast worked with movement coaches to study how real animals walk, tilt their heads, and react to humans. The challenge was to make the animals look convincing while still allowing the audience to notice the human awkwardness inside the costumes. The actors later joked that the suits were so hot and heavy that even simple movements felt like an intense workout, but the effort paid off because those exaggerated, slightly clumsy motions became some of the funniest moments in the film.

Also Known As: hachijianha , Haechijianha , I Won't Hurt You , We Don’t Hurt You , 超＂人＂氣動物園

Genres: Comedy, Drama
Tags: Zoo Setting, Animal, Workplace Setting, Zoo Director Male Lead, Attorney Male Lead, Single Male Lead, Personality Change, Financial Scandal, Bankruptcy, Break Up (Vote tags)
Country: South Korea
Type: Movie
Release Date: Jan 15, 2020
Duration: 1 hr. 57 min.

Stuck in a dead-end temp position at a renowned law firm, attorney-at-law Tae Soo dreams of one day landing a permanent position there. One day, he is given a special job to revitalize a failing zoo. The problem is, there aren't any animals. Moreover, he has exactly 3 months to do so.

With the zookeepers' help, he comes up with a brilliant idea of having the zookeepers dress up as animals. One by one, the zookeepers put on animal suits and masks and become polar bears, tigers, gorillas, and sloths. The new zoo opens and Tae Soo's polar bear goes viral when a video of him drinking a can of coke hits the internet.

Thanks to everyone's help, the zoo with fake animals is a massive hit and Tae Soo can now go back to the law firm with a permanent job. But before he leaves the zoo, he finds out what his law firm was planning with the zoo... Can Tae Soo come up with another brilliant idea to save not only himself but the zookeepers and the zoo?

description:
The centerpiece of the HAUS NOWHERE flagship store in Seoul is a massive, hyper-realistic animatronic dachshund named Sunshine that has completely redefined the concept of retail design. What makes this installation truly mind-blowing is the sheer level of detail crafted by the Gentle Monster robotics lab. Unlike typical statues, Sunshine is designed to mimic the subtle biological rhythms of a living creature. As you stand next to it, you can see its chest rise and fall with slow, rhythmic breaths, its nose twitching as if it’s dreaming, and its eyelids fluttering in a state of deep sleep. This uncanny realism turns a high-end boutique into a surreal, emotional experience that stops shoppers in their tracks.

The story behind this giant pup is just as creative as its engineering. The installation was built to promote a new fragrance collection by Tamburins, a sister brand to Gentle Monster. According to the brand's narrative, Sunshine is a "giant dog that dreams of a race," which explains the sleek, futuristic silver armor it wears. The metallic suit contrasts sharply with the soft, realistic fur textures, blending high-tech sci-fi vibes with the cozy, familiar feeling of a napping pet. It’s a clever piece of marketing that associates the brand with innovation, warmth, and artistic daring.

What is most fascinating is how this reflects the "New Retail" trend dominating South Korea. Gentle Monster has effectively moved away from the idea that a store is just a place to buy glasses or perfume. Instead, they treat their retail space like a world-class art gallery where the products are almost secondary to the atmosphere. By placing a breathing, "living" giant in the middle of a shopping mall, they create a viral moment that stays with visitors long after they leave. It’s a perfect mix of advanced robotics and clever storytelling that makes you feel like you've stepped into a dream.

Original video credit: IG/liams_daily_life__.

What Looked Like Cruelty Became a Beautiful Act of Love
description:
A police officer is eating a hot dog when he passes by a hungry male dog and his puppies.
The hot dog accidentally falls to the ground.

Driven by hunger, the dog moves toward the food.
But the officer stops him, steps on the hot dog, picks it up, and throws it away.

The dog feels defeated.
He lies down beside his puppies, protecting them in silence.

Minutes later, everything changes.

What seemed like cruelty turns into compassion.
The officer returns, pushing a wheelbarrow filled with large containers of dog food and fresh water — enough for the father dog and all his puppies.

❤️ Sometimes love is misunderstood… until kindness reveals itself.

⚠️ This is a fictional AI-made video created for entertainment and reflection.

description:
Lors de la finale d’un championnat junior de jiu-jitsu, une scène choquante a marqué les spectateurs. La combattante en bleu, en grande difficulté face à son adversaire, n’arrivait pas à prendre l’avantage.
Sous la pression de l’enjeu, elle tente alors un geste strictement interdit, extrêmement dangereux. Heureusement, l’arbitre intervient rapidement et lui ordonne d’arrêter. 🥋⚠️

Mais malgré l’avertissement, elle répète le même geste quelques instants plus tard. Cette fois, les conséquences sont dramatiques. L’adversaire est gravement blessée, se fracture le dos et est contrainte de mettre fin à sa carrière sportive.
Heureusement, grâce au soutien de ses proches et de la communauté, elle commence peu à peu à aller mieux.

Une vidéo qui relance le débat sur la pression en compétition, le respect des règles, et les dangers des gestes interdits dans les sports de combat.

🔍 Mots-clés : jiu-jitsu, sport de combat, geste interdit, arbitre, blessure grave, finale junior, pression sportive, sécurité, compétition, accident sportif, carrière brisée, vidéo choquante, short YouTube, respect des règles, récupération.

title: Carlos Alcaraz a sauvé le tennis 🥹
description:
Carlos Alcaraz a sauvé le tennis 💪🏼

Parce que dans un match complètement lunaire, l'Espagnol s’est qualifié pour sa première finale de l’Open d’Australie face à un Zverev qui nous a fait du Zverev. 

Parce que je ne sais pas qui voulait voir l’Allemand se qualifier après ce match. Mené 2 sets 0, il a d’abord eu cette colère lorsqu’Alcaraz obtient un temps mort médical pour se faire soigner de crampes dans le 3e, et pour le coup, on comprend son coup de gueule, parce qu’il n’est normalement pas autorisé d’obtenir des soins pour crampes au tennis. 

Mais là où on a le droit de s’interroger, c’est sur ce qu’on a vu sur le reste du match. Parce que pendant 3h, face à un Alcaraz touché et qui peinait à se déplacer, l’Allemand a voulu simplement voulu gérer alors qu’il aurait pu écraser l’Espagnol physiquement. 
Deux tie-break gagné dans la douleur pour remonter à 2 sets partout, un break d’avance même dans le 5e, au point de servir dans le match puis… le trou noir. Comme à son habitude, l’Allemand explose dans sa tête, donne des points facile en attendant la faute d’Alcaraz, perd 4 jeux consécutifs et envoie le numéro 1 mondial en finale après 5h27 de match.

Un nouveau choke à ajouter à son palmarès, et de nouveaux regrets à digérer pour celui qui aura bien du mal à enlever son étiquette d’éternel looser.

Messi signs a camera and gives it to a fan, turning it into a high value item worth $150,000. The next day, the fan uses the money to buy a BMW. When it’s Ronaldo’s turn, he takes off his jersey and throws it into the crowd, and a fan catches it. Ronaldo’s jersey is worth $4,000,000, and the next day the fan uses that money to buy a Bugatti.

description:

Les Lyonnais enchaînent ainsi une huitième victoire consécutive toutes compétitions confondues, avec une prestation collective solide et une efficacité offensive remarquable.
Grâce à ce succès, l’OL conforte sa 4ᵉ place au classement avec 36 points, poursuivant son objectif de rester dans le haut du championnat et de maintenir sa régularité sur tous les fronts.

title: 24H DANS MA VIE DE MAMAN et ENTREPRENEUSE (mdr)
description:
Merci à Qonto, l’entreprise française qui vous accompagne gratuitement dans
la création de votre entreprise. Pour toute nouvelle création d’entreprise, recevez
50 € sur votre compte en utilisant le code SHERA50 :
https://qonto.com/fr/creation?utm_source=influence&utm_medium=shera&utm_campaign=fr_fr_marketing_influence_youtube_shera_company-creation_january_2026

Nouveau 24h sans filtre dans ma vie de maman et d’entrepreneuse. Les premières semaines de janvier ont été… chaotiques mdr 
Entre la neige, le vent, Popeye et les enfants, on peut dire que l’année a commencé sur les chapeaux de roues !
Malgré tout, j’ai quand même réussi à avancer sur tout ce que j’avais à faire : briefings avec mes équipes, tournages, rangements de mes bureaux, events, et vie perso. Ce n’est pas parfait, mais c’est la vraie vie, et finalement c’est ça qui compte le plus !!! 
J’espère que ce vlog vous plaira et qu’il vous fera du bien,une pause feel good pour commencer l’année mes stars :) 
Merci d’être là, et on se retrouve la semaine prochaine ❤️

title: İki Günlük Vlog. Ecrin Su Çoban. Telefon Satın aldım. Ananeme Sürpriz. Karma'yı Arabesk Söylesem.
description:
Ara tatil bitmeden çok istediğiniz vloglardan biri olan iki günlük vlogu sizler için çekmek istedim. Öncelikle kırılan telefonumun yerine yenisini almak için bir alışveriş merkezine gitmek üzere hazırlandım. Pembiş bir kombin giydim. Alışveriş merkezinde bir kaç mağaza gezip fiyatları değerlendirdik. Aklımıza yatan mağazadan kendime yeni bir telefon aldım. Babamla yemek yedik. Eve geldiğimde telefonumun aktarma işlemlerini yaptım. Bu işlem oldukça uzun sürdü. Bu esnada annemin telefonuyla arkadaşlarımı darladım. Daha sonra kardeşlerimle bir şeyler içmek için dışarı çıktım. Dönüşte Bengü ile birlikte eve geldik. Bengü ve Hüseyin ile birlikte terasta eğlenceli vakit geçirdik.  Yatmadan önce acıktığım için kendime makarna pişirip yedim. Sonrada yatıp uyudum.
   Ertesi gün saçlarıma cila attırmak için kuaföre gittim. Kuaför çıkışı İlke ile birlikte  anneanneme çiçek alıp doğumgününün kutladım. İlke ile birlikte sistemden yeni dönem derslerimizi seçtik. Sonrasında kardeşim Hüseyin'in parçalanmış telefonunu yenilemek için telefon almaya gittik.  Eve döndüğümüde gelen bir kargoyu açtım. içinden kaybolan yıldız kolyemin aynısından çıktı. siz sevgili takipçilerimden biri bana yensini alıp göndermiş. Çok şaşırdım ve çok mutlu oldum. Kolyemi takıp hazırlandım. Arkadaşlarımla dışarıya çıktım. yemek yiyip vakit geçirdik. Eve dönünce saç ve yüz bakımımı  yaptım. 
Umarım videomu beğenirsiniz.

We’re back at That ’70s House to transform my hallway! This space in my house has undergone some other projects, and in this video, I’m attempting to bring it all together cohesively. The inspiration is, as always, MCM and retro, so we’re going with a statement wood accent wall, adding a gorgeous thrift flip as a sideboard, and attempting to create the illusion of a hidden door. description:
عمري ما كنت حابة نشارك ولدي في السوشيال ميديا 🤍
كنت كنفضّل نخليه بعيد، محمي، وفي عالمو الصغير 🌸

اليوم ولدي كبر، وقريب يلتحق بالمدرسة 📚
وما بقاتش عندي كيفاش نزيد نخبه، خصوصاً ملي كيتشاركوا صورو وهو مع باباه، في أماكن عامة، ولا حتى في گروبات، أو إلا بان بالغلط…
الخلاصة، الولد كبر وما بقاتش عندي السيطرة على كل شي 💛

من هنا قررت نكون أنا اللي حاضرة،
نشارك بإرادتي وبحدودي ✨
أحسن من أن نكون معرّضة للاستفزاز أو المضايقات من ناس مجهولة 🌷

شكراً لكل الناس اللي كيحبوني، وكيحمسوني، وكيقدّرو يشوفوا هاد اللحظات الصغيرة ❤️
ولليوم دايماً كيسولوني: “واش كي يشبه للصينين ولا للمغاربة؟” 😅💛

#movie 🔪 Betrayal and Brutality: The Infamous Stabbing Scene from "Chopper"
description:
The ultimate act of betrayal happens when violence comes from the one you trust most. In this scene breakdown, we're diving into one of the most raw and shocking moments from the gritty Australian crime biopic, "Chopper" (2000). This film pulls no punches in its portrayal of notorious criminal Mark "Chopper" Read, but this particular scene delivers a gut-wrenching blow—literally.

The Setup: A Tense Reunion
The scene builds on a classic yet volatile dynamic: the tense reunion between old friends. Mark "Chopper" Read (played with unnerving intensity by Eric Bana), now out of prison, meets up with a former friend and associate. There's history here—shared time behind bars, old scores, and the unspoken rules of the criminal world. The atmosphere is thick with unspoken threats and past grievances. Chopper, ever the provocateur, might be testing boundaries, while his friend simmers with a resentment that's about to boil over.

The Betrayal: When a Friend Becomes the Weapon
What makes the violence so impactful is its origin. This isn't a random act from a stranger; it's a calculated, deeply personal attack from someone who was once considered a "good friend". The argument escalates, and in a flash, the friend produces a knife. The ensuing attack is brutal, frenzied, and visceral. Chopper is stabbed multiple times—a relentless assault that is as much about emotional betrayal as it is physical harm. The cinematography doesn't glorify the violence; it traps you in the chaos, making you feel the shock and the violation of trust.

Why This Scene is Iconic

Eric Bana's Breakout Performance: This scene is a masterclass in Bana's physical commitment. He portrays the shock, the adrenaline-fueled survival instinct, and the profound hurt of betrayal with terrifying authenticity.

The Core of Chopper's Myth: This moment is pivotal to understanding Chopper Read's legend. It's a key incident that fuels his paranoia, his ruthless reputation, and the cycle of violence that defines his life. It shows that in his world, even the closest bonds can be severed with a blade.

More Than Just a Stabbing: The scene transcends a simple act of violence. It's a dark exploration of loyalty, power, and the fragile codes of the underworld. It asks a haunting question: what happens when the rules break down and the person you'd trust with your life is the one trying to end it?

This brutal betrayal is a cornerstone of the film's exploration of crime not as glamour, but as a brutal, isolating, and psychologically damaging way of life.

What do you think is the ultimate betrayal in cinema? Is it worse when it comes from a friend or a loved one? Let us know your thoughts in the comments below.

If you're fascinated by the gritty, true-crime stories that Hollywood rarely tells, be sure to LIKE, SUBSCRIBE, and hit the bell for more deep dives into the most hard-hitting scenes from cult classics and biopics.

The UNLIKELIEST Superhero Tryouts | Zoom's Academy Scene
description:
Video Description:

Forget the Justice League. This superhero team is recruited from detention! In the 2006 comedy Zoom, a secret government program needs to train a new generation of heroes. Their leader, former hero Captain Zoom, is tasked with finding candidates with a specific genetic marker.

He finds them in the most unexpected place: a group of misfit teenagers. One by one, they are brought to the underground academy. Watch the hilarious and surprising moment each kid reveals their unique, often clumsy power: one can run at supersonic speed but can't stop, another has super-strength tied to his emotions, a girl can turn invisible when she's embarrassed, and another can manipulate objects with her mind.

Their "tryout" is pure chaos—a perfect mix of slapstick and super-powered potential. Against all odds, this ragtag group of outcasts is officially enrolled as Earth's new last line of defense. It’s a funny, feel-good clip about finding power where you least expect it.

Why Watch?

· Fun Superhero Twist: A lighthearted, comedic take on the classic "hero origin" story.
· Underrated Cast: Features a young cast including Kate Mara and a fun performance from Tim Allen.
· Pure 2000s Fun: A nostalgic dose of family-friendly action-comedy.

#movie Hubert Fiorentini vs. Three Goons | Wasabi (2001) Fight Scene Breakdown
description:
Hey everyone, and welcome back to the channel! In today's scene breakdown, we're diving into a classic action-comedy from the early 2000s that blends French bravado with Japanese chaos. We're looking at "Wasabi" (also known as The Avenging Fist or Green Mustard), starring the legendary Jean Reno.

This 2001 film, written by the master of Euro-action Luc Besson, follows Hubert Fiorentini (Jean Reno), a tough, no-nonsense Parisian cop with a notoriously short fuse and a heavy heart over a lost love. When he travels to Tokyo to settle the affairs of his late ex-girlfriend, he gets the shock of his life: he has a 19-year-old daughter, Yumi (played by Ryoko Hirosue). His mission to reconnect with her is immediately hijacked when they discover Yumi is the target of violent Japanese yakuza, who are after a massive fortune left in her name.

The Scene: A Father's Instincts Kick In
The clip we're breaking down today is a perfect example of Hubert's character. He's trying to have a normal day with his newly discovered, shopping-obsessed daughter in the bustling streets of Tokyo. However, his sharp cop instincts immediately sense they are being followed by hostile figures.

What unfolds is a masterclass in efficient, brutal action. Three yakuza enforcers, thinking they have the upper hand, move in to confront or kidnap Yumi. They severely underestimate the man beside her. In a flash, the shopping bags are dropped. The gentle, awkward father persona vanishes, and the hardened police detective takes over.

Why This Fight is Iconic

Character in Action: This isn't just a random fight. It visually communicates Hubert's core trait: he protects what's his with overwhelming force. It's his violent, love language.

Comedic Contrast: The scene thrives on the stark contrast. One moment it's a quirky father-daughter outing, the next it's a whirlwind of precise, painful-looking takedowns. The comedy comes from the sheer nonchalance with which Hubert dispatches the threat before returning to "dad mode".

Jean Reno's Presence: No one does "gruff exterior with a secret soft spot" quite like Jean Reno. He brings a physical credibility and a weary, "I don't have time for this" attitude that makes the action both cool and funny.

A Nod to Léon: For fans of Reno's iconic role in Léon: The Professional, this film and this scene feel like a fun, alternate-universe sequel where the protector finally gets a happy, action-packed family life.

This scene sets the tone for the entire film: a chaotic, funny, and heartfelt journey where a French bruiser uses his very particular set of skills to clean up the Tokyo underworld for the sake of family.

What's your favorite Jean Reno action role? Is it Hubert from Wasabi, the iconic Léon, or someone else? Let's chat in the comments below!

#movie A King's Man's Daring Escape | "The Goat Pull" Scene Breakdown
description:
Forget high-tech gadgets—this might just be the most unconventional, utterly ridiculous, and weirdly brilliant escape plan in Kingsman history!

In this wild scene from The King's Man, the film that explores the origins of the iconic Kingsman spy organization during World War I, the hero finds himself in a desperate situation . It perfectly captures the series' signature blend of high-stakes action and dark comedy.

Here, Orlando, the Duke of Oxford (played by Ralph Fiennes), is trapped on the side of a sheer cliff after a brutal fight with the film's villain . With options running out, survival comes down to sheer wit... and the help of an unlikely ally. In a moment of pure, inspired desperation, he uses a mountain goat as his unlikely ladder, stepping on its back and pulling on its horns to hoist himself to the top of the cliff .

This scene is a prime example of how this prequel film differentiates itself. While forgoing the futuristic weapons of the later films, it delivers jaw-dropping action through wildly creative and sometimes illogical physical feats set against the backdrop of the Great War . It's a tense, funny, and completely unexpected moment that reminds us why we love this franchise.

What to Watch For:

The Setup: The brutal fight on the clifftop that leaves the hero dangling for his life.

The "Solution": The calm yet absurd moment of realization as Orlando spots the goat and formulates his plan.

The Execution: The sheer physicality and suspense of the climb.

The Aftermath: The now-iconic moment where, having reached safety, he shares a long, bewildered stare with the goat that just saved him .

Don't forget to LIKE, SUBSCRIBE, and hit the BELL for more breakdowns of the most inventive, funny, and badass scenes from your favorite action movies!

What did you think of this scene? Was it genius or just plain silly? Let us know in the comments below!

#movie 🔪 Betrayal and Brutality: The Infamous Stabbing Scene from "Chopper"
description:
The ultimate act of betrayal happens when violence comes from the one you trust most. In this scene breakdown, we're diving into one of the most raw and shocking moments from the gritty Australian crime biopic, "Chopper" (2000). This film pulls no punches in its portrayal of notorious criminal Mark "Chopper" Read, but this particular scene delivers a gut-wrenching blow—literally.

The Setup: A Tense Reunion
The scene builds on a classic yet volatile dynamic: the tense reunion between old friends. Mark "Chopper" Read (played with unnerving intensity by Eric Bana), now out of prison, meets up with a former friend and associate. There's history here—shared time behind bars, old scores, and the unspoken rules of the criminal world. The atmosphere is thick with unspoken threats and past grievances. Chopper, ever the provocateur, might be testing boundaries, while his friend simmers with a resentment that's about to boil over.

The Betrayal: When a Friend Becomes the Weapon
What makes the violence so impactful is its origin. This isn't a random act from a stranger; it's a calculated, deeply personal attack from someone who was once considered a "good friend". The argument escalates, and in a flash, the friend produces a knife. The ensuing attack is brutal, frenzied, and visceral. Chopper is stabbed multiple times—a relentless assault that is as much about emotional betrayal as it is physical harm. The cinematography doesn't glorify the violence; it traps you in the chaos, making you feel the shock and the violation of trust.

Why This Scene is Iconic

Eric Bana's Breakout Performance: This scene is a masterclass in Bana's physical commitment. He portrays the shock, the adrenaline-fueled survival instinct, and the profound hurt of betrayal with terrifying authenticity.

The Core of Chopper's Myth: This moment is pivotal to understanding Chopper Read's legend. It's a key incident that fuels his paranoia, his ruthless reputation, and the cycle of violence that defines his life. It shows that in his world, even the closest bonds can be severed with a blade.

More Than Just a Stabbing: The scene transcends a simple act of violence. It's a dark exploration of loyalty, power, and the fragile codes of the underworld. It asks a haunting question: what happens when the rules break down and the person you'd trust with your life is the one trying to end it?

This brutal betrayal is a cornerstone of the film's exploration of crime not as glamour, but as a brutal, isolating, and psychologically damaging way of life.

What do you think is the ultimate betrayal in cinema? Is it worse when it comes from a friend or a loved one? Let us know your thoughts in the comments below.

If you're fascinated by the gritty, true-crime stories that Hollywood rarely tells, be sure to LIKE, SUBSCRIBE, and hit the bell for more deep dives into the most hard-hitting scenes from cult classics and biopics.

title: Pourquoi Pierre Niney m'a donné son mouchoir usagé ?
#POV : Quand tu réponds enfin aux questions de ta majorité 🎂
description:
#POV: When you finally answer the questions of your adulthood 🎂. Today, I’m celebrating my 18th birthday. The living room is decorated with pink balloons and sparkles, my friends are laughing in the corner, and my mom is serving cakes and fruit juices. But in my heart, there’s a little empty hole – for months, my parents have been asking me the same questions, the ones about adulthood: “What do you want to do after school?”, “Are you going to move out alone?”, “Do you already have a plan for your future?” And every time, I lower my head, change the subject, because I had no answers.
I thought adulthood was having all the answers, being strong, being able to make decisions without hesitation. But me, at 18, I’m still confused: I love drawing, but my parents think it’s a “hobby”; I want to stay with them a little longer, but everyone tells me that “it’s time to grow up”; I don’t know what I want to do with my life, and it terrifies me.

The party is in full swing when my mom calls me into the kitchen, her hand held out to me. “Come, my daughter, we need to talk,” she says, her voice soft, without the pressure I expected. I approach, hands shaking, ready to hear those questions I can’t answer again. But she doesn’t ask me anything – she takes me in her arms and says: “I know you’re confused, that you don’t have all the answers. And that’s okay.”

She makes me sit on a stool, and she tells me about her 18th birthday: “When I was 18, my parents asked me the same questions. I didn’t know what I wanted to do either, I was afraid of making a mistake, I wanted to stay little forever. But adulthood isn’t having all the answers – it’s having the courage to look for them.”

In that moment, something changes in me. I look at my mom, her eyes full of tenderness, and I realize – #POV: When you finally answer the questions of your adulthood 🎂. I still don’t know what I want to do with my life, but I know I can draw, I can learn, I can make mistakes and get back up. I don’t want to move out alone now, and there’s nothing to be ashamed of – I want to enjoy these moments with them, before spreading my own wings.

“Mom,” I say, my voice steady and confident, “I still don’t know what I want to do after school, but I want to try art, drawing. I want to stay with you for another year, to learn, to prepare. And when I’m ready, I’ll leave, but I know you’ll always be here.” My mom smiles, tears in her eyes, and hugs me tighter: “That’s the best answer you could give me, my daughter.”

I go back to the living room, hands raised, shouting: “My friends! Today, I finally answered the questions of my adulthood 🎂! I don’t know everything, but I know what I want to try!” Everyone laughs, winks, and we keep celebrating – not just my 18th birthday, but also that moment when I stopped fearing adulthood, and learned to accept it, with all my questions and my dreams.

description:
Profitez de 20 euros offerts en ETF avec Trade Republic sur ce lien ► https://trade.re/ludoc20
Conditions: créditez 100€ et faire 3 investissements sous 21 jours  
Investir comporte des risques, notamment le risque de perte de capital. Les performances passées ne préjugent pas les performances futures. Collaboration commerciale avec Trade Republic. Conditions et informations disponibles sur l'application Trade Republic

Episode 1 : https://youtu.be/XexpNOZHh7g

Synopsis :

La prise d’otages dans le plus grand studio de youtubeurs dégénère, le forcené devient de plus en plus fou et agressif. Plusieurs médias dévoilent l’existence d’une deuxième otage cachée. La BRI et les sapeurs pompiers n’ont plus le choix et doivent lancer un assaut d’urgence. 

Le 12 juin 2018, au cœur de Paris, une prise d’otages éclate dans les bureaux de Mixicom, l’agence de Cyprien, Squeezie et de plusieurs des plus grands youtubeurs français. Ce qui ressemble d’abord à un acte de folie isolé révèle rapidement un tout autre scénario : le forcené n’est pas là par hasard, il vise les créateurs de l’agence.

À travers les témoignages exclusifs des survivants, des négociateurs de la BRI, des enregistrements audios et des archives inédites, cette série documentaire reconstitue minute par minute le déroulement de ces quatre heures de siège. Un récit sous haute tension qui explore les mécanismes de la violence, la fascination pour la notoriété et les limites de la justice face à la maladie mentale.

Avec les interventions de Adrien Gabeaud, Christophe Molmy, Nicolas de la BRI, Georges Salinas, Sandrine Larremendy, Franck Bonnier, David-Olivier Reverdy, Johanna Rozenblum, Karine Jean, Christian Sainte, Michel Delpuech, Rudy Reichstadt, Dr Bilal Bendid, Dr Vincent Mahé et Christophe de la Police Judiciaire.

Les enregistrements audio, les images de l'intervention, les vidéos des riverains et les extraits télévisés présentés dans ce documentaire sont authentiques. Certaines images de vidéosurveillance et vues aériennes sont des reconstitutions basées sur des recherches et des témoignages directs. Les noms de certains intervenants ont été volontairement masqués afin de préserver leur anonymat, conformément à leur souhait.

Dans un monde où la puissance magique est déterminée par des emblèmes de naissance, le sage Gaius est le plus puissant du monde. Cependant, il estime que son emblème n'est pas adapté au combat pur. Pour devenir encore plus fort, il décide de se réincarner des milliers d'années dans le futur.

The UNLIKELIEST Superhero Tryouts | Zoom's Academy Scene
description:
Video Description:

Forget the Justice League. This superhero team is recruited from detention! In the 2006 comedy Zoom, a secret government program needs to train a new generation of heroes. Their leader, former hero Captain Zoom, is tasked with finding candidates with a specific genetic marker.

He finds them in the most unexpected place: a group of misfit teenagers. One by one, they are brought to the underground academy. Watch the hilarious and surprising moment each kid reveals their unique, often clumsy power: one can run at supersonic speed but can't stop, another has super-strength tied to his emotions, a girl can turn invisible when she's embarrassed, and another can manipulate objects with her mind.

Their "tryout" is pure chaos—a perfect mix of slapstick and super-powered potential. Against all odds, this ragtag group of outcasts is officially enrolled as Earth's new last line of defense. It’s a funny, feel-good clip about finding power where you least expect it.

Why Watch?

· Fun Superhero Twist: A lighthearted, comedic take on the classic "hero origin" story.
· Underrated Cast: Features a young cast including Kate Mara and a fun performance from Tim Allen.
· Pure 2000s Fun: A nostalgic dose of family-friendly action-comedy.

💬 Which "unlikely" superpower from a movie would you want the most? Let us know in the comments! 👇

Stuka dive-bombers shatter the earth, artillery turns trenches into graves, and then the true horror arrives: a rolling wave of Panzer tanks in a deadly wedge formation. They crash through barbed wire, crush bunkers, and their machine guns mow down young cadets like wheat. 😨🔥

What follows is a slaughter of heartbreaking, futile heroism. 🫡

Anti-tank gunners are obliterated the moment they fire.

Cadets with bundles of grenades charge forward, only to be cut down by machine-gun fire before they can reach their target.

Officers scream orders to blow the bridges, sending sappers on suicide missions through a storm of steel.

This scene is a visceral, brutal, and tragic depiction of mechanized warfare — where youth and courage are ground to dust under tank treads. 🎬⚙️💔

title: CNews invente un complot halal dans nos assiettes
description:
Quand une chaîne d’information sérieuse consacre un segment à la « menace » du gigot d’agneau halal… on touche le fond de la désinformation médiatique. Sur CNews, un invité nommé Bruno affirme sans rire que son plat était insipide parce qu’il était halal — et pire encore, suggère qu’il s’agissait peut-être de viande halal, confirmé selon lui par un « invité musulman ». Oui, vous lisez bien. Derrière cette séquence devenue virale pour son absurdité culinaire se cache une stratégie bien plus inquiétante : celle de transformer l’islam en ennemi domestique, invisible, tapi dans nos assiettes. Ce n’est pas du journalisme, c’est de la fabrication de peur — une islamophobie banalisée, servie au petit-déjeuner comme un croissant. Pourtant, les faits sont clairs : le halal n’altère ni le goût ni la texture de la viande, et un gigot sec, c’est souvent juste une question de cuisson… pas de complot religieux. Cette vidéo démonte avec ironie et rigueur ce faux débat qui vise à diaboliser des millions de Français·es au nom d’un fantasme identitaire. Parce que non, Bruno, le problème n’est pas votre agneau — c’est votre ignorance.

title: François Asselineau répond à vos questions en direct n°96
description:
François Asselineau répond en direct à des questions qui lui sont posées par des internautes.

Dans ses réponses, le président de l'UPR s’attache toujours à prendre du recul par rapport au simple commentaire, rapide et superficiel de l'actualité.

François Asselineau veille à replacer les sujets abordés dans leur contexte historique et géopolitique, il relie les événements aux forces sous-jacentes qui les orientent. 

Ceci explique la longueur de certaines réponses. Ce travail d'éducation populaire est très rarement fait par les autres responsables politiques ou par les médias.

———

Dans ce numéro 96, François Asselineau a répondu aux questions suivantes :

00:03:12 - Question n°1 de *Sylvie*
_Craignez-vous qu’une guerre se déclare entre l’Iran et le couple États-Unis/Israël, pensez-vous que cela puisse déboucher sur une 3e guerre mondiale ?_

00:29:40 - Question n°2 de *Nathan*
_La loi sur l'interdiction des réseaux sociaux aux moins de 15 ans, adoptée hier à l'Assemblée nationale, imposera de fait une vérification d’identité pour tous les internautes dès septembre 2026. Que pensez-vous de cette loi ?_

00:46:01 - Question n°3 de *Simon*
_Que pensez-vous du départ à la retraite anticipée de la directrice départementale de la Police Nationale des Landes, faisant suite à la manifestation agricole du 11 janvier dernier ?_

00:51:21 - Question n°4 de *@angelaurdiales5626*
_Que pensez-vous de l'accord commercial entre U.E et l’Inde ??_

01:17:24 - Question n°5 de *Nadine*
_À Davos Ursula Van der Leyen a annoncé la création du 28e état de l’UE qui harmonisera le droit du travail et des entreprises au sein de l’UE. Quelle est votre analyse de ce projet ?_

01:22:41 - Question n°6 de *Jérôme*
_Depuis quelque temps, le message du Frexit passe un peu plus sur les médias et n’est pas ridiculisé que ce soit sur CNews, France Info  ou comme des médias sur Internet grand  public comme Legend. Est-ce que vous sentez qu’il se passe quelque chose ?_

01:30:36 - Question n°7 de *Florian*
_Invité dans plusieurs grands médias, Nicolas Dupont-Aignan a présenté son programme pour 2027  : la sortie de la France de l'Union Européenne dans le but de refonder une autre Europe à 4 ou 5 États afin que la France ne se retrouve pas, je cite, "seule au milieu de l'Atlantique". Quel jeu joue-t-il ?_

01:36:40 - Question n°8 de *Nadine*
_Le 23 janvier, alors que Macron faisait son show à Davos, l’Allemagne et l’Italie signaient un pacte dans les domaines de la défense, de l’immigration, de la sécurité, de l’énergie, de la compétitivité. Le « couple franco-allemand » semble sur la voie du divorce ! Qu’est-ce que vous en pensez ?_

01:46:23 - Question n°9 de *Christian*
_Je viens de relever sur le site de la direction du Trésor, le solde de la balance Target2 s'élevant à un déficit pour la France de -1500 milliards. Le confirmez-vous? Si oui, comment la France peut-elle régler ce problème en cas de sortie de l’UE ?_

title: RN / GAUCHE : POUR QUI VOTENT VRAIMENT LES CLASSES POPULAIRES ?
description:
Soutenez Blast, nouveau média indépendant : https://www.blast-info.fr/soutenir

Les classes les plus précaires sont-elles les premières électrices de l’extrême droite ? Comment le RN parvient-il à séduire une frange de plus en plus bourgeoise de la société ? Les classes populaires sont-elles réellement divisées entre les bourgs et les tours, comme l’affirment certains ? Dans ce focus, les chercheurs Youssef Souidi et Thomas Vonderscher, auteurs de Nouvelles cartographie électorale Française, nous aident à y voir plus clair grâce à une analyse extrêmement fine des comportements électoraux français.

title: ILS SAVAIENT, ILS PARLENT ENFIN, ET QU'À MOITIÉ : LE SCANDALE MORANDINI FAIT CRAQUER CNEWS
description:
🔴 Soutenez le Média ! Le combat continue grâce à vous : https://www.lemediatv.fr/campagne

CNews traverse une crise interne autour du maintien de Jean-Marc Morandini à l’antenne malgré sa condamnations pour abus sexuels sur mineurs. La première à prendre position a été Sonia Mabrouk, mise au pied du mur par le député socialiste Jérôme Guedj. Elle exprime alors un malaise feutré tout en ménageant la direction. Ce qui n'a pas manqué de provoquer la colère de Serge Nedjar, le patron de CNews. 
Elle parvient toutefois à obtenir le soutien, encore plus mesuré, de Pascal Praud et de Laurence Ferrari. Tous adoptent un même compromis : dénoncer à demi-mots tout en affirmant leur loyauté à la direction. D'autres visages de la chaîne préfèrent un soutien aveugle, c'est le cas de Christine Kelly ou encore du RN. Derrière cette mise en scène de malaise, c’est tout le système d’obéissance et de compromission qui apparaît : les animateurs font semblant d’être outrés pour l’image, mais encaissent leur chèque, conscients que la vraie liberté d’expression s’arrête là où commencent les intérêts du patron.

Le Récap est un édito politique, à retrouver du lundi au jeudi sur Le Média.

title: A Minneapolis, cette photo montre comment Trump a militarisé sa chasse aux migrants
description:
Des tenues d'inspiration militaire, des armes dignes d'un théâtre de guerre... Telle est l'apparence des hommes de la police de l'immigration américaine dans une photo prise à Minneapolis lors de l'arrestation d'un homme de nationalité libérienne nommé Garrison Gibson.  L'image, prise le 11 janvier par le photojournaliste John Locher, continue d'être relayée pour illustrer la militarisation de la chasse aux migrants menée par Donald Trump.  Une photo analysée en détail par le "New York Times", qui explique en quoi les agents fédéraux de l'ICE bénéficient d'un matériel de pointe, conçu initialement pour les champs de bataille ou les unités d'élite.
